<!--- Technologies -->

<h2>Technologies</h2>

<home-features style="align-items: normal;">

<home-feature>
  <home-icon icon="&#xf121;"></home-icon>
  <h4>SLING</h4>
  <p>SLING is an open source project under an Apache license and all the code is
  available on GitHub. SLING is written mostly in C++ but can be used from Python
  by using the SLING Python API (pysling). There is also a JS module so you can
  use SLING in the browser.
  </p>
  <home-button href="https://github.com/ringgaard/sling" label="SLING on GitHub"></home-button>
</home-feature>

<home-feature>
  <home-icon icon="&#xf1c0;"></home-icon>
  <h4>SLINGDB</h4>
  <p>SLINGDB is a lightweight persistent key-value database with a HTTP
  interface. It can be installed independently of the other SLING components
  and is distributed as a standalone Debian package.
  </p>
  <home-button href="https://github.com/ringgaard/sling/blob/master/doc/guide/slingdb.md" label="SLINGDB on GitHub"></home-button>
</home-feature>

<home-feature>
  <home-icon icon="&#xf1ec;"></home-icon>
  <h4>Myelin</h4>
  <p>Myelin is a JIT compiler for neural networks. It compiles neural network
  functions written in Python into optimized x64 assembly or GPU code at runtime.
  </p>
  <home-button href="https://github.com/ringgaard/sling/blob/master/doc/guide/myelin.md" label="Myelin on GitHub"></home-button>
</home-feature>

</home-features>

